title: West Midlands Police head resigns over controversial ban on Israeli football fans
description: A British police chief behind the decision to ban Israeli soccer fans from a match in England has resigned.  Craig Guildford has stepped down immediately as the head of the West Midlands force following mounting pressure on him to quit over the controversy.  Last year, the police chief recommended that fans from the Israeli soccer team Maccabi Tel Aviv be banned from attending a European match against Aston Villa in a part of the UK with a high Muslim population.  A report found the decision to ban Tel Aviv fans overstated the threat posed by them.

title: Controversy surrounds Ugandan vote amid claims of election misconduct
description: A prominent candidate in Uganda's presidential election has allegedly been forcibly taken by the country's security forces.   Bobi Wine is challenging Yoweri Museveni, who has ruled the country for 40 years.  Authorities report the president has so far won 75 per cent of the votes.  The election in the central African nation has been plagued by allegations of voter suppression.

title: Ukrainian children face hypothermia amid winter energy shortages
description: Children in Ukraine are at increased risk of hyperthermia this winter due to Russia's ongoing war in the country, according to UNICEF.  Russia has been attacking Ukraine's energy infrastructure, prompting President Volodymyr Zelensky to declare a state of emergency earlier this week.  International aid agencies warn that children are facing hypothermia as emergency power generators run low.

title: Crocodile snatches woman’s hat and swims away
description: A fishing enthusiast named Polly Lamond had her favorite hat snatched by a crocodile at Leaders Creek, northeast of Darwin, Australia.

title: Canada and China strike new trade deal
description: Canada and China have struck a new trade deal.  The friendly relationship is raising new worries over Beijing’s influence in North America.  The deal promises to lower tariffs on Chinese electric vehicles and Canadian canola oil.

title: Dashcam vision shows serious collision on the Bruce Highway
description: Dashcam vision has shown a car and a truck collide on the Bruce Highway.  The crash caused the Bruce Highway to close for seven hours.  The incident happened just after 10 am in the northbound lanes.

title: US announce Gaza ‘Board of Peace’
description: The White House has announced the formation of a ‘Board of Peace’ to supervise the temporary governance of Gaza as part of Trump's 20-point peace plan to end the war.

title: Biologists explore unique genetic makeup of Antarctic animals
description: The biology of species in the Antarctic is very different as the temperature of the water drastically changes their world.  The ocean in the Antarctic is still below freezing temperatures.

title: Hazardous surf warning issued for NSW coast
description: A hazardous surf warning has been issued for the NSW coast from Eden in the south to Newcastle in the north.

title: Donald Trump has done ‘a lot of good things’ since coming to power
description: The Courier Mail Columnist Des Houghton says US President Donald Trump has done “a lot of good things” since coming to power.

title: Endangered freshwater turtles growing in number after successful breeding season
description: There are calls for celebration after three species of endangered freshwater turtle breeds are growing.  This comes after a hugely successful breeding season.

title: Trump has ‘taken a flamethrower’ to the progressive elites
description: The Courier Mail Columnist Des Houghton says US President Donald Trump has “taken a flamethrower” to the progressive elites.

title: Severe cold snap caused waterways to freeze along Hungary’s northern border
description: A drone has recorded a ship moving through sheets of ice in the Danube in Hungary.  A severe cold snap has caused many waterways to freeze and disrupt shipping.  The video shows the icebreaker working to protect cargo ships from the pressure of the ice along Hungary’s northern border.

title: More than 700 SES volunteers in NSW battle severe weather
description: More than 700 SES volunteers are out in the field in New South Wales, attending over 900 jobs as the state battles severe weather.

title: Donald Trump seeming ‘unstoppable’ at the moment
description: The Courier Mail Columnist Des Houghton says US President Donald Trump is seeming “unstoppable” at the moment.
